    <div class="text"><p>
    <br/>
    	The game was designed to last 3 days, Monday to Wednesday with the game beginning and ending at midnight. Nonetheless, the event was such a huge hit, nearly all the eggs had been found by the end of Monday! After the first day, the front-runner had found 200 eggs! People had woken up at midnight to go find these eggs! Not just one or two mind you, nearly 60 people were patrolling the campus! Our advertising worked so well people were very upset to find that most of the eggs were found so quickly. The old adage you snooze you lose is very applicable here. From a community perspective, the event was incredibly impactful. Students from every corner of campus were talking about the egg hunt and connecting with other people. Our winners at the end came from all over the University. We almost immediately were given clearance to double the size of the event next year, with many people already counting down to the next hunt. No doubt the next iteration will be even more competitive and even more fun for those involved. Naturally, the only way an event can be this big of a success is when a lot of great people work together. I’d like to thank Vic Collum for all of her hard work, as well as every person who came to help set up and hide the eggs!
    <br/><br/>
    Onwards and Upwards!
    </p>
